Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine, marked proteinuria), hypoglycemia, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria). Liver and electrolyte parameters are within normal limits. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Findings are suggestive of acute or chronic kidney disease with possible nephrotic features; clinical correlation and further nephrological evaluation are recommended.
